{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9c4ae1d3-bf52-4388-8c62-5a866d2d44ea","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's a general guide. NuGet trusted publishing uses OIDC so your workflow never stores a long-lived API key.\n\n### What to change\n\n**1. Add `id-token: write` permission** to the job (required for OIDC):\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      contents: read\n      id-token: write   # ← needed for OIDC token\n```\n\n**2. Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step.** Remove the `--api-key` flag and add `--source` with the trusted publisher endpoint:\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# After\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nThe OIDC token is passed automatically — no secret needed.\n\n**3. Register your repo as a trusted publisher on nuget.org:**\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a GitHub Actions publisher, specifying your **repository owner**, **repo name**, and optionally the **workflow file name** and **environment**.\n\n**4. (Recommended) Use a GitHub Environment** for an extra layer of protection:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    environment: nuget-publish   # gates deploys with approvals/rules\n    permissions:\n      contents: read\n      id-token: write\n```\n\n**5. Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret** from your repo settings once everything works.\n\n### Summary of changes\n\n| Area | Old | New |\n|---|---|---|\n| Auth | `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC (`id-token: write`) |\n| `dotnet nuget push` | `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | no key flag needed |\n| nuget.org config | API key in account | Trusted publisher entry |\n\nIf you share your workflow file I can make the exact edits for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"904b68e5-95b2-4ea4-8c63-294f5a162a5e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the repository. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to OIDC trusted publishing in GitHub Actions. I can provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":599,"requestId":"FE11:3F33F0:12E8CBC:153BAF8:6A066E8C"},"id":"efad7f7a-3ca7-421a-89b8-d03c8ac2d9a1","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:46.802Z","parentId":"7fa01776-ab8a-4ea8-8550-01f8ee131d53"}
